name: hymn of the bricklayer
description:
come on Henri, i know what would lift you from yer gloom. a round on the house and a rendition of that bricklayer tune!

-

november 6th, 2021

ghetto gates torn down.
feat of strength,
bricklayer with muscle all about,
walked up to those black iron bars,
and pulled them apart.
yes, this fair mannered constructor,
forever popular in form of 
tavern song, freed us from our
isolation, free to mingle outside 
of these practically prison encampments,
cause the soot skinned bricklayer
saved the day.

-
